sect1.para:
According to Patterson et al. (
               2012
            ), crucial conversations are necessary when stakes are high. For example, a relationship may be affected, a job loss could occur, a financial transaction may be disrupted, and a business deal upended. Current research supports that when organizations create cultures whereby crucial conversations are embraced, more patient lives are saved within hospitals, financial institutions gain loyal customers and have more financial gains, technology firms can with ease enhance functionalities internationally, and nuclear power plants operate safely (Patterson et al., 
               2012
            ). Crucial conversations will involve high stakes, opposing opinions, and strong emotions.
